**Abstract:**
Working notes examining whether Aquinas was a rationalist, challenging Wolterstorff's defense of Aquinas against charges of rationalism. Argues that while Aquinas was not an extreme post-Cartesian evidentialist, he was still an evidentialist in matters of reason and his theory of Scriptural language reveals rationalist assumptions. Includes analysis of Aquinas's Summa Theologica on sacred doctrine.

